<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Settting a 'border-spacing' width on a table</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/tables.html#separated-borders" />
        <meta name="flags" content="image" />
        <meta name="assert" content="The border-spacing width can be specified for a table (example from spec section 17.6.1)." />
        <style type="text/css">
            table
            {
                border: outset 10pt;
                border-collapse: separate;
                border-spacing: 15pt;
            }
            td
            {
                border: inset 5pt;
            }
            td.special
            {
                border: inset 10pt;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <table>
            <tr>
                <td class="special">&nbsp;</td>
                <td>&nbsp;</td>
                <td>&nbsp;</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>&nbsp;</td>
                <td>&nbsp;</td>
                <td>&nbsp;</td>
            </tr>
        </table>
        <p>Test passes if the table above is similar to the table below (cell widths have similar relative proportions).</p>
        <div>
            <img alt="Illustration of border spacing" src="../support/separated_border_model_005.png" />
        </div>
    </body>
</html>